BEGIN_PGML To find the smallest number of moves required to transport 5 disks to another pillar, let's try to relate this task to the task of moving 4 disks. How many moves do each of the following tasks require? a. Move the 4 smallest disks to the second pillar: [_]{15}{5} moves.
a. Move the largest disk to the third pillar: [_]{1}{5} moves.
a. Move the 4 smallest disks to the third pillar (on top of the largest disk): [_]{15}{5} moves.
Therefore, the smallest number of moves required to move five disks is: [_]{31}{5}
END_PGML
Section::End();
